                    <ul style="color: #666; margin-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li>Binary format with 56-byte header (Magic: "K2SH")</li>
                        <li>Section-based architecture (metadata, image pyramid, hotspots, data layers)</li>
                        <li>Feature flags system for optional sections</li>
                        <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>src/core/format_spec.py</code>, <code>src/core/encoder.py</code>, <code>src/core/decoder.py</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Breakthrough 2: SSIM-Based Pyramid Selection -->
            <div class="info-card" style="margin-bottom: 30px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1) 0%, rgba(118, 75, 162, 0.1) 100%); border-left: 5px solid #667eea;">
                <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #667eea; margin: 0; flex: 1;">2. SSIM-Based Image Pyramid Format Selection</h3>
                    <span style="background: #667eea; color: white; padding: 5px 12px; border-radius: 15px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: bold;">‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê GENUINE INNOVATION</span>
                </div>
                <p style="color: #666; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <strong>What it is:</strong> Multi-resolution image pyramid (2048, 1024, 512, 256px) with automatic format selection per level using SSIM (Structural Similarity Index) and Shannon entropy analysis.
                </p>
                <p style="color: #666; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <strong>Why it's innovative:</strong> First implementation of SSIM-guided format selection in an image pyramid. Uses perceptual similarity (SSIM ‚â• 0.995) to decide if lossy compression is acceptable. 
                    Adaptive quality - high-res levels can be lossless, lower-res can be lossy if visually similar.
                </p>
                <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05); padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 15px;">
                    <p style="color: #333; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px;">Technical Details:</p>
                    <ul style="color: #666; margin-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li>SSIM threshold: 0.995 (very conservative - 99.5% similarity)</li>
                        <li>Entropy threshold: 5.0 bits/symbol</li>
                        <li>Format selection: PNG (lossless) or JPEG/WEBP (lossy) per level</li>
                        <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>src/core/encoder.py</code> lines 125-254</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div style="background: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ffc107; padding: 15px; margin-top: 15px; border-radius: 8px;">
